Sec. 74.2035. TRANSFER OF FUNDS BETWEEN ERADICATION ZONES AND
MAINTENANCE AREAS. Notwithstanding any provision of this subchapter
or Subchapter D, with the approval of the board and the commissioner,
the foundation may transfer funds, including the proceeds from the
collection of assessments or maintenance fees, between active
eradication zones and maintenance areas as needed to fulfill the
purposes of this subchapter and Subchapter D. The board shall
consult with affected cotton grower steering committees before
recommending that the commissioner approve the transfer of funds
under this section.
Added by Acts 2013, 83rd Leg., R.S., Ch. 577 (S.B. 818), Sec. 7, eff.
June 14, 2013.

